                                "stop": 8.013,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 137550,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has our opinion this morning in case 08-1322, Astrue Vs Ratliff."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.013,
                        "stop": 201.143,
                        "byte_start": 137550,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15100,
                            "name": "Clarence Thomas",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/clarence_thomas",
                            "last_name": "Thomas",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2744,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 688194000,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2744"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32680,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49064,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/clarence_thomas.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8870,
                            "identifier": "clarence_thomas"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.013,
                                "stop": 15.281,
                                "byte_start": 137550,
                                "byte_stop": 166599,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on a writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Eighth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.281,
                                "stop": 20.783,
                                "byte_start": 166599,
                                "byte_stop": 188646,
                                "text": "Petitioner Michael Astrue is United States Commissioner of Social Security."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.783,
                                "stop": 31.315,
                                "byte_start": 188646,
                                "byte_stop": 230755,
                                "text": "Respondent Catherine Ratliff is an attorney represented her client in a successful lawsuit against the Commission for Social Security benefits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.315,
                                "stop": 65.521,
                                "byte_start": 230755,
                                "byte_stop": 367637,
                                "text": "Because Ratliff\u0027s client prevailed under claim that the district court granted the unopposed motion Ratliff filed for award of attorney\u0027s fees under Section 204 (d) of the Equal Access to Justice Act or EAJA, codified at 28 U.S.C., Section 2412 (d). Before the government paid the fees award however, it discovered that Ratliff\u0027s client owed the United States a debt that predated the award."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 65.521,
                                "stop": 80.81,
                                "byte_start": 367637,
                                "byte_stop": 428763,
                                "text": "Accordingly the United States notified that district court, that it planned to exercise its statutory authority to withhold payment of the fees award as an offset against that debt."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.81,
                                "stop": 104.122,
                                "byte_start": 428763,
                                "byte_stop": 521968,
                                "text": "Ratliff intervened and objected to the proposed offset on the grounds that EAJA makes an attorney\u0027s fee award payable directly to the prevailing litigant\u0027s attorney and thus such awards cannot be offset to debts owed by the litigant to the government."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 104.122,
                                "stop": 118.647,
                                "byte_start": 521968,
                                "byte_stop": 580065,
                                "text": "The district court rejected this argument, but the Court of Appeals reversed, holding that EAJA makes the attorney\u0027s fees, in this case, payable directly to Ratliff, the attorney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.647,
                                "stop": 124.221,
                                "byte_start": 580065,
                                "byte_stop": 602425,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the clerk today, we reverse the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 124.221,
                                "stop": 130.079,
                                "byte_start": 602425,
                                "byte_stop": 625831,
                                "text": "The party\u0027s dispute is governed by Section 24 (d) (1) (A) of EAJA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.079,
                                "stop": 140.209,
                                "byte_start": 625831,
                                "byte_stop": 666373,
                                "text": "That provision states in pertinent part that a court shall award to a prevailing party the attorney\u0027s fees at issue here."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 140.209,
                                "stop": 155.27,
                                "byte_start": 666373,
                                "byte_stop": 726559,
                                "text": "We have long held that the term prevailing party in attorney\u0027s fees statutes is a legal term of art that refers to the prevailing litigant not to the prevailing litigant\u0027s attorney."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 155.27,
                                "stop": 163.79,
                                "byte_start": 726559,
                                "byte_stop": 760728,
                                "text": "We conclude that the term carries the same settled meaning in Section 2412 (d) (1) (A) of EAJA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.79,
                                "stop": 193.584,
                                "byte_start": 760728,
                                "byte_stop": 879846,
                                "text": "We base this conclusion on the plain text of the statute and on our precedence and reject for the reasons set forth in our opinion, Ratliff\u0027s arguments that the Court of Appeals contrary judgment is supported by other provisions of EAJA along with certain provisions of the Social Security Act and the government\u0027s practice of paying fees awards directly to attorneys in some Social Security cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.584,
                                "stop": 201.143,
                                "byte_start": 879846,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Sotomayor has filed the concurring opinion in which Justices Stevens and Ginsburg have joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
